162
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:47,380
Work is equal to force times distance, and so there's a little bit of work that's done.

163
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:48,680
And what's the work that's done?

164
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:54,180
The work is equal to the force on the wall, this is the work of the force, times the distance

165
00:10:54,180 --> 00:11:07,400
that it's displaced, and that's equal to the pressure times the area times little dx.

166
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:13,720
The area times dx, this is the area of, let's say, this side of the box over here.

167
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:16,680
This is the area of this side of the box over here.

168
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,600
The box expands.

169
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:26,160
The area times dx, that's the change in volume of the box.

170
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,260
Alright?

171
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:34,140
So the work done is the pressure times the change in the volume of the box.

172
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:37,860
A times dx is the change in the volume of the box.

173
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:42,100
That's of course a famous equation, I just want to write it down because I like it.

174
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:45,680
Alright, what happens to the energy in the box?

