191
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:53,780
The change in the energy of the box is equal to two terms, just ordinary calculus.

192
00:12:53,780 --> 00:13:03,740
The energy density times the change in volume plus the volume times the change in the energy

193
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:05,860
density.

194
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:08,140
Both things change in general.

195
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:10,580
Both things change when you expand the box a little bit.

196
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:14,980
The energy density changes, certainly, and the volume changes.

197
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:15,980
The net change in the energy density changes.

198
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:25,940
The energy is the sum of two of them, and that has to be equal to minus the pressure

199
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:27,460
times dV.

200
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:34,260
Okay, but now let's plug in the hypothetical equation of state, something we haven't really

